\
The first suspicions of manipulation were declared by the Wall Street Journal around May 2008 after investigating the reliability of the panel banks' statements. Nevertheless, these suspicions were not solid given the lack of evidence in statistical terms. The publication of \\cite\{abrantesmetz2012\} detailed analysis of the LIBOR rate during the crisis with different barometers of confidence such as other short- term risk-free rates (OIS Curve, CDS Curve, 3-month US sovereign T-bill yield curve) ~\\ref\{fig:plot5\}.\\newline\
