\\subsubsection*\{England: Sterling Overnight Index Average (SONIA)\}\
\
The SONIA index was introduced as part of the new benchmark overnight index to replace LIBOR. It is published by the UK FCA (Financial Conduct Authority) in conjunction with the Bank of England and is calculated on the basis of short-term overnight transactions in the wholesale unsecured market where there is minimal credit, liquidity or other risk \\cite\{boe2017\}. The major advance in the reform concerns the methodology for calculating the index. With the new reform, the index is now calculated each business day on the basis of a truncated average rounded to four digits on eligible trades over \'a325 million* \\cite\{boe2017\}.\\newline\
